1. Start the Chatbot with tmux
Create a tmux session
tmux new -s chatbot

Run the Streamlit app
streamlit run app.py --server.port 8080 --server.address 0.0.0.0

You can now view your Streamlit app in your browser.


press:
Ctrl + B, then D
This detaches the session and leaves your app running in the background.

✅ The chatbot is now running 24/7 — you can safely close your SSH terminal.

2. Reattach to the Session (to Check or Update)

When you want to update or check logs:

tmux attach -t chatbot

You’ll see the running logs of your chatbot.

3. Stop the Running App

Inside the tmux session:

Ctrl + C

This stops the current Streamlit app but keeps you inside tmux.

4. Update the Code

While still inside tmux: 
git pull


If dependencies changed:
pip install -r requirements.txt

5. Restart the App

Start the app again:
streamlit run app.py --server.port 8080 --server.address 0.0.0.0


Once it starts successfully, detach again:
Ctrl + B, then D
✅ the chatbot now runs the newest version.
